  sodium: 400 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-n-spicy-apricot-chicken-67bd989a8b4d4424a2089d76
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated). Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

> Trim green beans if necessary or trim and discard woody bottom ends from asparagus. (Save broccoli for another use.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 6.

Meanwhile, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Swap in green beans or asparagus for broccoli; roast 12-15 minutes for green beans or 10-12 minutes for asparagus.

While broccoli roasts, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

TIP: If chicken cutlets are on the thicker side, reduce heat to medium and cover; cook ~{5-7%minutes} on second side.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Add @apricot jam{1%unit}, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, @Sriracha{1%tsp}, and 1⁄4 cup water to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in more water 1 tsp at a time.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%TBSP}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%TBSP}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise on a diagonal.

Divide chicken, broccoli, and rice between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.